	       <p>Senart notes that G and AS add fragments of one more line (of which he can discern nothing on the estampages): <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">sya ma</foreign> (AS <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">mā</foreign>) . . . . <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">sarva</foreign> (AS <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">sarva[ṃ]</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">rakṣāti</foreign> (AS <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">rakṣati</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">vidya</foreign> (AS <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">viṣṇ[udatā]</foreign>) . . . . . 
